benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Remove tags from bundle

covered: Valid Deletion: DELETE tests cover removal of all tags, specific tags, and handling of no-tags scenario.
Error Handling: Tests cover invalid bundle IDs, non-existent bundles, missing/invalid headers, and unauthorized access, plus service unavailability.
Query Parameters & Data Variants: Extensive coverage of tagDef variations (empty array, multiple, invalid, extra params) and large data scenarios (1000 tags).
Concurrency & Performance: Tests for concurrent deletions and timeouts address performance and race conditions.
Data Consistency: Integration checks ensure GET reflects removal after deletion.
Security/Headers: Tests around header validation and header content (X-Killbill-Reason/Comment, X-Killbill-CreatedBy) and XSS-injection in headers.
gaps: Pagination: No pagination tests for large tag datasets (not applicable to DELETE but part of guidelines).
Caching Behavior: No tests for ETag/Cache-Control semantics.
Rate Limiting: No explicit rate-limiting tests (bursty/high-frequency requests).
Soft Deletes: No tests addressing soft-delete semantics.
Forbidden Access: No explicit 403 Forbidden scenario tested.
Internal Server Errors: No test simulating 500 Internal Server Error (beyond 503).
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests where listing tags or large datasets are involved.
Introduce tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to simulate burst requests.
Include a test for 403 Forbidden when user lacks specific permissions.
Add a test simulating 500 Internal Server Error for server-side failures.
Strengthen accessibility testing with UI rendering of error messages for screen readers.
